  "text": "RSA is a well-known candidate for such a commutative encryption scheme; however, it is terribly inefficient, as it is recommended to use 2000-bit RSA modules in order to achieve reasonable security guarantee. RSA also needs to be modified to a private key scheme to gain the commutative property. For efficiency, we employ the PohligHellman exponentiation cipher [CITATION_1] with the same modulus and instantiate it in elliptic curve groups over F p . Let Param := (p, a, b, g, q, ζ) be the elliptic curve domain parameters, consisting of a prime p that specifies the finite field F p , two elements a, b ∈ F p that specifies an elliptic curve E(F p ) defined by the equation:",
